$interpreted: Maeok: How is Himawari doing?
Juan-Yun: She's calmed down... She's in her room, waiting for the representatives to finish their discussion.
Maeok: Their discussion...
Maeok: Juan-Yun, if you know something, you better spit it out.
Juan-Yun: Maeok, I promise you that I'm just as surprised and confused as everyone else... I only know that she's still my sister-in-law...
Shun: What about Qing-Feng? Where is he? I bet he knows something!
Juan-Yun: My father left to take care of some business before the tournament began...
Juan-Yun: Still, I don't think he knows anything. I take care of Himawari, he doesn't have much to do with her.
Bull Chieftain: Are you all really doubting the qilin chieftain? He's a mythic!
Panther Chieftain: Yeah, I'm sure if Qing-Feng knew anything, he'd have told us ages ago!
Shun: So now what? Juan-Yun doesn't know, Qing-Feng doesn't know, and Himawari's shut herself up in her room.
Shun: What are we supposed to do, forget this ever happened? Let her keep competing?
Maeok: ...I'm sure you all saw.
Maeok: Her necklace glows with every breath she takes.
Maeok: That's proof of her power, that she's a true leopard.
Toyokuni: ...And if she's strong enough to make it glow, then that's proof the holy talisman recognizes her as a competitor.
Maeok: That's right. And even if she's a human,
Maeok: It's our duty to support her until the end of the tournament.
Toyokuni: Then what about that other human? Miranda?
Toyokuni: She's already lost. We don't have any responsibility towards her anymore.
Toyokuni: And I bet she knows something, or she wouldn't have pulled on Himawari's tail. I say we find her and ask her some questions.
Soohyeon: Ah, I think she'll need some more time before she wakes up...
Maeok: Well if that's all we've got for now, then...
Maeok: We'll continue to support Himawari in the tournament while we wait for Miranda to regain consciousness.
Juan-Yun: Thank you, Arbiter Maeok. I'll let Himawari know.
Tindoiimu: Did Himawari have something to do with the yellow team's "accident"?
Juan-Yun: ...Looks like you were waiting for me.
Tindoiimu: I noticed you watching her when they broke the news.
Tindoiimu: You think she caused the rockfall, don't you?
Juan-Yun: ......
Juan-Yun: What are you trying to say?
Tindoiimu: She was lying to you this whole time, and you're still trying to protect her?
Juan-Yun: ...I already told you that family is my top priority.
Juan-Yun: I was serious when I said that. I hoped you would understand.
Tindoiimu: (...Of course I understand. Doesn't matter what they do, family will always be family.)
Tindoiimu: (That's why when you spouted that nonsense about the Alliance, and cooperation... I couldn't accept that...)
Tindoiimu: (...I won't.)
Tired Guard: Man I'm tired! Why's it our job to look after this human, anyway!?
Exhausted Guard: It is what it is. She's important, I guess... *yawn*
Head Assassin: Listen, I'll strike her chest, you two strike her head. This is gotta be a clean job. The boss doesn't want this getting out.
Assassin: Understood!
Head Assassin: We do it on three...
Assassin: Uhh... are you counting?
Head Assassin: What the... quick, run!
???: Three!
Law: Trying to assassinate my student!? Just can't wait for reincarnation, can you?
Law: I've dealt with them. You can get up now.
Head Assassin: Eh!? Wasn't she supposed to be passed out!?
Head Assassin: Damn, this is a trap!
Law: Trying to take the easy way out? I think not!
Maeok: Law!? When did you get here? What happened?
Law: These men were planning to assassinate Miranda.
Bull Chieftain: Huh? Isn't that Otoshi? He's Sennosuke's right-hand man!
Panther Chieftain: You idiot! Shut up!
Law: Sennosuke, hmm? Thank you very much for letting everyone know.
Law: And thank you, Miss Soohyeon, for assisting in my little performance.
Law: Sennosuke is quite the scoundrel, yet ever skilled at covering his tracks and evading the long arm of the law.
Law: Now, tonight, someone has been sent to end my student's life.
Law: Now that we have evidence, clear as day, will you all keep pretending that nothing is wrong?
Law: Arbiter!
Panther Chieftain: Arbiter, the way I see itâ€”
Maeok: Everyone, come with me back to the Alliance Hall. Summon Sennosuke to explain himself.
Seahorse Chieftain: Arbiter! Think carefully about this...
Maeok: No, you listen carefully to what I'm telling you!
Maeok: I'm the boss here. I'm the arbiter, and you do what I say!
Soohyeon: Wow... mom's so cool...
Toyokuni: It's rare for Arbiter Maeok to be so resolute... we should follow her orders.
Law: Good. This is more like the Maeok I know.
Law: Now, let us get to the bottom of this.
